  "messages": [
    {
      "id": "209cfea2ba844a3a9283f203da548a6ca05c3f48",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-12 08:47:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, approved\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nSince we are planning on making new layouts soon anyway, we could just define those with lu_fid instead of ost_id and avoid this complexity in the future.  I guess I'm OK to go back to the old lmm usage given that we want to get 2.4 out the door, and this would otherwise also cause some problems with older clients as well.\n\nIn hindsight, it was a mistake not to move from the \"IGIF FID\" format used in 1.8 (with {inode} == seq instead of \"id\") directly to use lu_fid here.  I only thought of that a couple of months ago, but it was too late by then since the change had been made for 2.1.0.\n\nPossibly at some point in the future we can have LFSCK convert the old LOV_MAGIC_V1/V3 layouts in the filesystem to the new format so that the use of ost_id can be removed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
